A zigzag is a pattern made up of small corners at variable angles, though constant within the zigzag, tracing a path between two parallel lines; it can be described as both jagged and fairly regular.
In geometry, this pattern is described as a skew apeirogon. From the point of view of symmetry, a regular zigzag can be generated from a simple motif like a line segment by repeated application of a glide reflection.

Another name for the pattern is "Herringbone" FYI ğŸ¤“

metadata.name: In Due Time #28
metadata.description:
â€œIn Due Timeâ€ is a collaborative generative collection between artists Melissa Wiederrecht and Amber Vittoria. Inspired by Wiederrechtâ€™s mastery of line and Vittoriaâ€™s notable palette, this 1/1/250 series captures the present moment. It serves as a reminder that we are more similar than we are different, leveraging homogeneous shapes to create distinctive compositions.

Vittoriaâ€™s poem for the collection:

â€œIn Due Timeâ€
We will all become
Particles dancing
Across the skyline.

The artwork listed is indeed authentic, created by, and copyright to artists Melissa Wiederrecht and Amber Vittoria; the purchase of this NFT is a purchase of the asset, not of the copyright.

-------------------------------------------

To save a high-resolution image for printing, click â€œopenâ€ under the image on the page for your token, and then hit:

Digits â€œ1â€ through â€œ9â€ to get an image that is 1000 through 9000px tall.  This may take a while, depending on the size and your computer, so please be patient.

metadata.name: Twistings #36
metadata.description:
âœ§ TWISTINGS âœ§

Twistings, the "Explore Variety" collection, explores the beauty & variety that is hidden within the simple math of Archimedean spirals.

There are seven different circular "entities", each brought forward by using slightly different mathematical settings of the spiral formulas: Drops, Circles, Fireworks, Flowers, Roses, Spirals & Twisters.

____

âœ§ CURATED / RANDOM âœ§

I love both the concept of a heavily curated set, hand picked by the artist, the best representation / the most beautiful, but also the concept of the larger, random collections showing the variety hidden within the algorithm.

I've therefore also released an "Artist Curated" collection of 7 pieces that I meticulously hand-picked from over 1000 outputs. You can find these on the platform 1stDibs.com/nft (under my name "nadieh"). They represent my favorite for each of the seven unique entities. A free mint of this "Explore Variety" collection will be airdropped to each buyer of a "Curated" piece.

____

âœ§ OPTIONS âœ§

n - Toggle grainy noise on/off (on by default, it's subtle to see)

s - Save the image at the current window size and pixel density

To save a larger image you can add the parameter `&pixeldensity=2` (or another number) to the end of the URL when viewed on the live page. Afterwards press "s" to save the image. The number is the factor with which the width and height are increased w.r.t. the current window size.

-- The larger the image / pixeldensity, the longer it will take to create & save --

____

âœ§ NOTES âœ§

It works best and fastest in Firefox!

As of the drop day there is a browser bug for Chrome on the ARM Apple laptops. It incorrectly visualizes certain color blend modes. The following color palettes are affected: Antique, Camping, Pastel, Prime & Rainbow. I hope/assume this will be fixed soon. 

____

Created by Nadieh Bremer
Twitter & Instagram: @NadiehBremer
Website: VisualCinnamon.com

metadata.name: Twistings #140
metadata.description:
âœ§ TWISTINGS âœ§

Twistings, the "Explore Variety" collection, explores the beauty & variety that is hidden within the simple math of Archimedean spirals.

There are seven different circular "entities", each brought forward by using slightly different mathematical settings of the spiral formulas: Drops, Circles, Fireworks, Flowers, Roses, Spirals & Twisters.

____

âœ§ CURATED / RANDOM âœ§

I love both the concept of a heavily curated set, hand picked by the artist, the best representation / the most beautiful, but also the concept of the larger, random collections showing the variety hidden within the algorithm.

I've therefore also released an "Artist Curated" collection of 7 pieces that I meticulously hand-picked from over 1000 outputs. You can find these on the platform 1stDibs.com/nft (under my name "nadieh"). They represent my favorite for each of the seven unique entities. A free mint of this "Explore Variety" collection will be airdropped to each buyer of a "Curated" piece.

____

âœ§ OPTIONS âœ§

n - Toggle grainy noise on/off (on by default, it's subtle to see)

s - Save the image at the current window size and pixel density

To save a larger image you can add the parameter `&pixeldensity=2` (or another number) to the end of the URL when viewed on the live page. Afterwards press "s" to save the image. The number is the factor with which the width and height are increased w.r.t. the current window size.

-- The larger the image / pixeldensity, the longer it will take to create & save --

____

âœ§ NOTES âœ§

It works best and fastest in Firefox!

As of the drop day there is a browser bug for Chrome on the ARM Apple laptops. It incorrectly visualizes certain color blend modes. The following color palettes are affected: Antique, Camping, Pastel, Prime & Rainbow. I hope/assume this will be fixed soon.

A zigzag is a pattern made up of small corners at variable angles, though constant within the zigzag, tracing a path between two parallel lines; it can be described as both jagged and fairly regular.
In geometry, this pattern is described as a skew apeirogon. From the point of view of symmetry, a regular zigzag can be generated from a simple motif like a line segment by repeated application of a glide reflection.

Another name for the pattern is "Herringbone" FYI ğŸ¤“

metadata.name: Arcadia #3 #4
metadata.description:
Night city has come! ğŸŒšğŸŒƒğŸ’«

Arcadia is a project where we work on the basis of a 3D world created from voxels with a 2D isometric rendering. The engine has been built using the p5.js library as the basis for many iterations of the project.

In this edition of Arcadia night comes to town! Playing with dark blue tones and dim lighting with warm colors, an attempt has been made to convey a feeling of warmth, peace and tranquility. New concepts have been included such as windows playing with the opacities of colors, roofs and new functions for the generation of buildings.

Improvements in performance and processing of the voxel engine have also been worked on, which have allowed the number of buildings to be increased.

metadata.name: the Horizon #89
metadata.description:
I am interested in and pay attention to repeating patterns in nature. Searching for the possibility of depicting this rhythm, texture, and space opens this opportunity as a new experience for me. And how can I convert time to image? In this work, I have depicted the circle of wandering, like the sun that fluctuates in every horizon and climate, sometimes hot and tense and sometimes its rays like the morning breeze caressing our face, calling us to a new beginning. Where is your sun on the horizon, and what time is it in your world?
Made in p5js
Created July 2022
Artist: @ChistaAi
